Rating: 4
I served this for potluck on Wednesday night at church. It was a big hit, even with the children whose parents said they wouldn't eat meatloaf. Some even asked for seconds!! I used a can of tomato soup for the chicken broth and can of tomato sauce. I doubled the Parmesan cheese an omitted the red pepper flakes as well. For the last 10 minutes of cooking I combined 1/2 cup of pasta sauce with 3 Tablespoons of light corn syrup and poured it over the top of the meatloaf. The combination of flavors was good and the meatloaf stayed nice and moist. I will definitely add this to my recipe box for many future meals.

