This turkey loaf was great! I did make a couple of alterations based on other reviews and what I had on hand. First off, I didn't cook the vegetables in white wine. I just sauteed them with a little I Can't Believe It's Not Butter spray. I doubled the garlic and I used whole eggs instead of just whites. I used vegetable broth instead of chicken broth. Instead of salt I added a couple of dashes of Worcestershire sauce. I also cooked the meat loaf in a muffin tin. The recipe as I made it gave me 11 "meat muffins." I served them with homemade ketchup (another epicurious recipe), and all my seven guests wanted seconds!

