I just made this yesterday and it was very delicious - contrary to many reviewers! This was my very first experience with meatloaf and I am keeping this recipe. I followed the recipe almost exactly, except I used 2 whole eggs instead of egg-whites and a little more parmesan cheese. I used ground turkey. Also, I cookied it for 1hr, then emptied out (mostly) all of the liquid around the meatloaf carefully(there was a lot!) and then cooked it for another 30 more minutes. This recipe is light and tasty.

Rating: 4
Great higher fiber, lower fat version of an all-American favorite. But for the novice cook, it's not a no-fail recipe. A cook has gotta use your judgement on this one. This is my judgment: Saute your veggies, but don't add the liquid if it didn't cook off. Soak the oats for 5-10 min in broth, and dump excess broth. Don't add the broth called for in the recipe. Use a meat mix, such as 1/2 lean beef and 1/2 turkey. Comes out super every time. If this is one of your first meatloaves, don't start here.

